==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: leaf-cutter
<hw>leaf-cutter</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of various species of wild bees of the
genus <gen>Megachile</gen>, which cut rounded pieces from the edges of
leaves, or the petals of flowers, to be used in the construction of
their nests, which are made in holes and crevices, or in a leaf rolled
up for the purpose. Among the common American species are <spn>Megachile
brevis</spn> and <spn>Megachile centuncularis</spn>. Called also
<altname>rose-cutting bee</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> leaf-cutting bee, leaf-cutter bee.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Leafed</ent>⟦br⟧
